						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">How much current does a PS/2 mouse for PCs draw? I'm trying to figure out whether a PS2 to SNES adapter with a microcontroller inside would be feasible.<br /></div> As a data point, my optical PS/2/USB one is rated for maximum 100mA. Non-optical mice will be much lower, but making it clear to the user that they need to use a crappy cheap ball mouse might be difficult. A random source claims that the original PS/2 port has a fast-blow single-time fuse set to 275mA, although later ones at least used a polyfuse instead.</div>

